                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1224.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Marines and bluejackets landed yesterday afternoon at about 4 o’clock after
                    Captain E. L. Beach had delivered a letter from Admiral Caperton addressed to
                    the committee of safety stating that the landing was entirely friendly and for
                    the preservation of order and protection of legations, etc. Conference today at
                    the Legation with the committee of safety and an agreement made that this
                    committee would disarm all Haitian soldiers before tomorrow night. City quiet
                    now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
